From daf7c7941463f3e1f62a32ab754b6ce33b0e8f12 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Danek Jiri <jirkadanek@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 23:04:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Refactor Profdiff CLI for concurrent REST API integration

Changes:
* Add thread safety: Implement deepCopy() constructors for core data classes and add synchronized to getMethodOrCreate() and addCompilationFragment() to prevent race conditions during caching.
* Stabilize fragment IDs: Change fragmentId from sequential integers to String hashes of the inlining path so IDs stay the same across API requests.
* Optimize parsing: Split tree parsing into independent loadInliningTree() and loadOptimizationTree() methods to allow lazy loading.
* Improve API support: Add getHotMethodsNames(), add getters/setters for caching and diffing logic, and change the Writer constructor to protected for easier extension.
